        public ImmutableSortedArrayPropertyMapBuilder<K,V> merge(ImmutableSortedArrayPropertyMapBuilder<?,? extends V> entries)

      • build

        public ImmutableSortedArrayPropertyMap<K,V> build()
        Build the immutable map. Validates all keys and values added, including sorting the keys and values, and checking for duplicate keys and values as necessary.

        Repeated calls to a builder containing a non-zero number of entries will return distinct map instances.

        Returns:
        an ImmutableSortedArrayPropertyMap containing the elements in the builder
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - there was a duplicate key or value specified in the builder
